# üê≥ Docker Command Cheat Sheet

A concise and practical list of the most important Docker commands for everyday use.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è 1. General Information

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `docker version` | Show Docker client and server versions | `docker version` |
| `docker info` | Display system-wide information | `docker info` |
| `docker help` | Show available commands or help for a specific command | `docker help run` |

---

## üì¶ 2. Images

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `docker pull <image>` | Download an image from Docker Hub | `docker pull nginx` |
| `docker images` | List all local images | `docker images` |
| `docker rmi <image>` | Remove a local image | `docker rmi nginx` |
| `docker build -t <name> .` | Build an image from a Dockerfile | `docker build -t jose/api .` |
| `docker tag <image> <repo>:<tag>` | Tag an image with another name or version | `docker tag jose/api jose/api:v1` |
| `docker push <image>` | Push an image to Docker Hub (requires login) | `docker push jose/api:v1` |

---

## üöÄ 3. Containers

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `docker run <image>` | Create and start a container | `docker run ubuntu` |
| `docker run -it <image> bash` | Run a container interactively with a shell | `docker run -it ubuntu bash` |
| `docker ps` | List running containers | `docker ps` |
| `docker ps -a` | List all containers (running + stopped) | `docker ps -a` |
| `docker stop <id>` | Stop a running container | `docker stop 7f5e1a` |
| `docker start <id>` | Start a stopped container | `docker start 7f5e1a` |
| `docker restart <id>` | Restart a container | `docker restart 7f5e1a` |
| `docker rm <id>` | Remove a container | `docker rm 7f5e1a` |
| `docker logs <id>` | Show container logs | `docker logs 7f5e1a` |
| `docker exec -it <id> <cmd>` | Execute a command inside a container | `docker exec -it nginx bash` |
| `docker inspect <id>` | Display detailed info about a container or image | `docker inspect nginx` |

---

## üìÇ 4. Volumes (Data Persistence)

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `docker volume create <name>` | Create a new persistent volume | `docker volume create data` |
| `docker volume ls` | List all volumes | `docker volume ls` |
| `docker volume rm <name>` | Remove a volume | `docker volume rm data` |
| `docker run -v <volume>:<path>` | Mount a volume inside a container | `docker run -v data:/var/lib/mysql mysql` |

---

## üåê 5. Networks

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `docker network ls` | List all networks | `docker network ls` |
| `docker network create <name>` | Create a new network | `docker network create my_net` |
| `docker network connect <net> <container>` | Connect a container to a network | `docker network connect my_net nginx` |
| `docker network inspect <name>` | Inspect network details | `docker network inspect bridge` |

---

## üßπ 6. System Cleanup

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `docker system prune` | Remove unused data (containers, images, networks) | `docker system prune` |
| `docker image prune` | Remove unused images only | `docker image prune` |
| `docker container prune` | Remove stopped containers | `docker container prune` |

---

## üîê 7. Authentication

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `docker login` | Log in to Docker Hub | `docker login` |
| `docker logout` | Log out from Docker Hub | `docker logout` |

---

## üß† 8. Useful Monitoring Commands

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `docker stats` | Real-time resource usage (CPU, RAM, etc.) | `docker stats` |
| `docker top <id>` | Show running processes inside a container | `docker top nginx` |
| `docker inspect <name>` | Display JSON details for debugging | `docker inspect nginx` |

---

## üß© 9. Docker Compose (Multi-Container Apps)

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| `docker compose up -d` | Start services defined in `docker-compose.yml` | `docker compose up -d` |
| `docker compose down` | Stop and remove services | `docker compose down` |
| `docker compose ps` | List running services | `docker compose ps` |
| `docker compose logs` | Show logs from services | `docker compose logs` |

---

## ‚ö° 10. Quick Daily Commands (Top 10)

```bash
docker pull nginx
docker run -d -p 8080:80 nginx
docker ps
docker logs <id>
docker exec -it <id> bash
docker stop <id>
docker rm <id>
docker images
docker rmi <image>
docker system prune
